<DocsLayout title="buoy tokens" description="Generate design tokens from your codebase">
  <h1>buoy tokens</h1>

  <p>
    Generate design tokens from values detected in your codebase. Outputs to
    CSS variables, JSON, Tailwind config, or AI-friendly context.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>

  <pre><code>buoy tokens [options]</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Option</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>-o, --output &lt;path&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Output file path (auto-detected if not specified)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--format &lt;format&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Output format: css, json, tailwind, ai-context (auto-detected)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--dry-run</code></td>
        <td>Preview without writing files</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--prefix &lt;prefix&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Prefix for CSS custom properties (e.g., "ds-")</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Examples</h2>

  <h3>Generate CSS variables</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy tokens --format css

:root {
  --color-primary: #3b82f6;
  --color-secondary: #64748b;
  --spacing-sm: 8px;
  --spacing-md: 16px;
  --spacing-lg: 24px;
}</code></pre>

  <h3>Generate Tailwind extension</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy tokens --format tailwind -o tailwind.tokens.js</code></pre>

  <h3>Generate AI context</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy tokens --format ai-context

Use for AI agents to understand available tokens with usage context.</code></pre>

  <h2>Output Formats</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>css</strong> - CSS custom properties (:root variables)</li>
    <li><strong>json</strong> - Standard JSON token format</li>
    <li><strong>tailwind</strong> - Tailwind CSS theme extension</li>
    <li><strong>ai-context</strong> - Markdown with token intent and usage</li>
  </ul>

